result.execSummary:
The defendant Mickail Sean Batchelor was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess w/Intent-Cocaine (>1-5g), a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1m)(cm)1r.
  • Carry Concealed Weapon, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 941.23(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Mickail Sean Batchelor in court with attorney Ann T. Bowe.  Jacob Daniel Corr appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, Defense and Defendant.  Additional statement made by Quintin B. 

AS TO COUNT 1:
The Court sentenced defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT in the Wisconsin State Prisons for 5 YEARS.  INITIAL CONFINEMENT of 2 YEARS and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 3 YEARS, with credit for 5 DAYS time served.  Court STAYED sentence and placed the defendant on PROBATION for a period of 3 YEARS with the following conditions for probation and extended supervision:
Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and is eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  
-Defendant to pay Court costs and all applicable surcharges and assessments out of cash bail on deposit.  Remaining balance to be returned to person who posted. 
-Defendant is to provide a DNA sample and pay the related surcharge out of cash bail on deposit.  Remaining balance to be returned to person who posted. 
-No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause
-Cooperate with agent
-Cooperate with any correctional programs recommended
-Follow all rules of probation and extended supervision
-Pay all supervision fees 
-Obtain/maintain full-time employment or full-time school
-AODA assessment and any recommended treatment
-Absolute sobriety with random urine screens and breathalyzers
-No alcohol or controlled substances

AS TO COUNT 2:
Court ordered defendant serve 60 DAYS in the House of Corrections, straight time, concurrent with 15CF880, consecutive to COUNT 1.  Defendant to report to the House of Corrections on April 28, 2016 at 5:00 p.m.
